## Pi runtime metadata

`audit_metadata` returns the exhaustive, authoritative Pi provenance block. In any session
that authors a durable record, call it once and paste its output verbatim. Add nothing else:
no `Username`, no `Co-Authored-By`, and no derived, guessed, or hand-written fields.

The block contains `Authored-By`, `Model`, `Model-Provider`, `Model-Gateway` when present,
`Session-ID`, and `Hostname`. It reports the root session's identity, automatically propagated
through subagent launches, and is callable from both root and worker sessions. Its output is
the only valid source for every field in the block; do not add `(source: ...)` suffixes.

`git commit` and `gh pr create` remain direct and un-intercepted: nothing attaches this block
or blocks publication if it is omitted. This is a manual, cooperative requirement.
